Decision control:-Decision controls are used for decision making. In C language there are **following** types of decision controls.

1.If statement
2.if-else statement
3.ladder if-else statement 
4.nested if-else statement 
5.switch statement

1.IF :- If is a keyword , which works as decision control.We attach a condition with if statement.If given condition is true then **if block** code will be executed otherwise it do nothing.

Syntax:-
if(condition){
    //code
}

2.If-else:-if-else is variation of if statement.We attch a condition with id statement. If given condition is **true** then **if block code** will be  executed and if given condition is **false** then **else block code** will be executed.

Syntax:-
if(condition){
    //if block code executed
}                                                       //this is called if-else constructor
else{
    //else block code execute
}

3.ladder if-else:-If you have many conditions and you want to execute code based on those conditions then you can use ladder if-else.

Syntax:-
if(condition1){
    //code1 executed
}
else if(conditon2){
    //code2 executed
}
else{
    //code3
}

4.Nested If-Else:-if  we use if-else construct in if block or else block or both blocks ,then it is called nested if-else.

1.Use of if-else in if block:-
if(condition1)
{
    if(condition2){
        //code1
    }
    else{
        //code2
    }
}
else
{
    //code3
}
2.Use of if-else inside else block:-
if(condition1)
{
//code1
}
else
{
    if(condition2)
    {
    //code2
    }
    else
    {
        //code3
    }
}

3.Use of if-else constructor in both block:-
if(condition1)
{
    if(condition2)
    {
        //code1
    }
    else
    {
        //code2
    }
}
else
{
    if(condition3)
    {
    //code3
    }
    else
    {
    //code4
    }
}

5.Switch:-Switch is keyword , which works as case control .It is use to create a menu based program.

syntax:
switch(expression)  //in C language in expression we use only int or char or enum
                    //in C++ language in expression we use int or char or short or enum or long etc.
                    //in java language in expression we use only int or char or short or byte or enums orstring.
{
case 1:
//code 1
break;                      //keywords-switch,case,break,default
case 2:
//code 2
break;              
case 3:
//code 3
break;
default:
//code 4
break:
}